      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Cultural Hero</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David Cuthbert lettr on Michael Kimmelman's July 30 article holds Van Kliburn captured public imagination as few classical artists ever did (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I wonder if younger readers today realize the kind of crossover culture hero Van Cliburn was after winning the Tchaikovsky competition. Mr. Cliburn captured the public imagination as few classical artists ever did, demonstrating that art could be the lingua franca between ideologies in fierce opposition.</p>
        <p>DAVID CUTHBERT  New Orleans</p>
      </block>
